  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "lesson-001",
      "courseId": "course-001",
      "title": "Skimming for Main Ideas",
      "order": 1,
      "durationMinutes": 45,
      "content": "Skimming is a reading technique that allows you to quickly get the main idea of a passage without reading every word.\n\n## Key Techniques:\n1. Read the title and headings first\n2. Look at the first and last sentence of each paragraph\n3. Pay attention to bold or italicized words\n4. Don't stop for unknown vocabulary\n\n## Practice Tips:\n- Set a timer for 2 minutes per passage\n- Focus on understanding the overall message\n- Practice with newspaper articles daily"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-002",
      "courseId": "course-001",
      "title": "Matching Headings Strategy",
      "order": 2,
      "durationMinutes": 50,
      "content": "Matching Headings is one of the most common question types in IELTS Reading.\n\n## Step-by-step Approach:\n1. Read all the headings first\n2. Underline keywords in each heading\n3. Read the first two sentences of each paragraph\n4. Match the main idea, not individual words\n\n## Common Traps:\n- Headings that share vocabulary with the paragraph but have a different meaning\n- Distractors that are too specific or too general"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-003",
      "courseId": "course-001",
      "title": "True / False / Not Given",
      "order": 3,
      "durationMinutes": 55,
      "content": "True/False/Not Given questions test your ability to identify whether information in the passage agrees with, contradicts, or is not mentioned.\n\n## Rules:\n- TRUE: The statement agrees with the information in the passage\n- FALSE: The statement contradicts the information\n- NOT GIVEN: There is no information about this in the passage\n\n## Strategy:\n1. Read the statement carefully\n2. Find the relevant section in the passage\n3. Compare word-by-word\n4. Don't use your own knowledge — only use what's in the text"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-004",
      "courseId": "course-002",
      "title": "Predicting Answers Before Listening",
      "order": 1,
      "durationMinutes": 40,
      "content": "Prediction is a powerful technique that helps you focus during the listening test.\n\n## How to Predict:\n1. Use the time before each section to read the questions\n2. Underline keywords and think about what type of answer is needed\n3. Predict possible answers based on the context\n\n## Example:\nQ: The library is open from ____ to 5pm.\nPrediction: A time in the morning (e.g., 8am, 9am)"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-005",
      "courseId": "course-002",
      "title": "Note Completion Techniques",
      "order": 2,
      "durationMinutes": 45,
      "content": "Note completion requires you to fill in missing information from what you hear.\n\n## Key Tips:\n1. Check the word limit (e.g., NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS)\n2. Read the notes before listening to understand the topic\n3. Listen for synonyms — the audio often paraphrases\n4. Write exactly what you hear, don't change the form"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-006",
      "courseId": "course-003",
      "title": "Opinion Essay Structure",
      "order": 1,
      "durationMinutes": 60,
      "content": "An Opinion Essay asks you to give your personal opinion on a topic.\n\n## Structure:\n1. Introduction: Paraphrase the question + state your opinion\n2. Body Paragraph 1: Main reason + example\n3. Body Paragraph 2: Second reason + example\n4. Conclusion: Restate your opinion\n\n## Band 7+ Tips:\n- Use a range of linking words\n- Include specific examples\n- Avoid repeating the same vocabulary"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-007",
      "courseId": "course-004",
      "title": "Part 1: Introduction & Interview",
      "order": 1,
      "durationMinutes": 30,
      "content": "Part 1 of the IELTS Speaking test lasts 4-5 minutes.\n\n## Common Topics:\n- Work/Study\n- Hometown\n- Hobbies\n- Daily routine\n\n## Tips:\n- Give extended answers (2-3 sentences)\n- Don't give one-word answers\n- Use a variety of tenses\n- Speak naturally, don't memorize scripts"
    },
    {
      "id": "lesson-008",
      "courseId": "course-004",
      "title": "Part 2: Long Turn (Cue Card)",
      "order": 2,
      "durationMinutes": 35,
      "content": "In Part 2, you receive a topic card and have 1 minute to prepare, then speak for 1-2 minutes.\n\n## Strategy:\n1. Use the 1-minute preparation time wisely\n2. Make brief notes on the card\n3. Cover all bullet points on the card\n4. Add personal details and examples\n\n## Practice:\nRecord yourself speaking for 2 minutes on random topics daily."
    }
  ],
